nested_items.name: reports
nested_items.description: The array of Report objects returned by BatchGetReports.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the report run.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The type of the report that was run.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the report that was run.

nested_items.name: reportGroupArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the report group associated with this report.

nested_items.name: executionId
nested_items.description: The ARN of the build run that generated this report.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of this report.

nested_items.name: created
nested_items.description: The date and time this report run occurred.

nested_items.name: expired
nested_items.description: The date and time a report expires. A report expires 30 days after it is created. An expired report is not available to view in CodeBuild.

nested_items.name: exportConfig
nested_items.description: Information about where the raw data used to generate this report was exported.

nested_items.name: exportConfigType
nested_items.description: The export configuration type. Valid values are:
S3: The report results are exported to an S3 bucket.
NO_EXPORT: The report results are not exported.

nested_items.name: s3Destination
nested_items.description: A S3ReportExportConfig object that contains information about the S3 bucket where the run of a report is exported.

nested_items.name: bucket
nested_items.description: The name of the S3 bucket where the raw data of a report are exported.

nested_items.name: bucketOwner
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services account identifier of the owner of the Amazon S3 bucket. This allows report data to be exported to an Amazon S3 bucket that is owned by an account other than the account running the build.

nested_items.name: path
nested_items.description: The path to the exported report's raw data results.

nested_items.name: packaging
nested_items.description: The type of build output artifact to create. Valid values include:
NONE: CodeBuild creates the raw data in the output bucket. This is the default if packaging is not specified.
ZIP: CodeBuild creates a ZIP file with the raw data in the output bucket.

nested_items.name: encryptionKey
nested_items.description: The encryption key for the report's encrypted raw data.

nested_items.name: encryptionDisabled
nested_items.description: A boolean value that specifies if the results of a report are encrypted.

nested_items.name: truncated
nested_items.description: A boolean that specifies if this report run is truncated. The list of test cases is truncated after the maximum number of test cases is reached.

nested_items.name: testSummary
nested_items.description: A TestReportSummary object that contains information about this test report.

nested_items.name: total
nested_items.description: The number of test cases in this TestReportSummary. The total includes truncated test cases.

nested_items.name: statusCounts
nested_items.description: A map that contains the number of each type of status returned by the test results in this TestReportSummary.
(string) ---
(integer) ---

nested_items.name: durationInNanoSeconds
nested_items.description: The number of nanoseconds it took to run all of the test cases in this report.

nested_items.name: codeCoverageSummary
nested_items.description: A CodeCoverageReportSummary object that contains a code coverage summary for this report.

nested_items.name: lineCoveragePercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of lines that are covered by your tests.

nested_items.name: linesCovered
nested_items.description: The number of lines that are covered by your tests.

nested_items.name: linesMissed
nested_items.description: The number of lines that are not covered by your tests.

nested_items.name: branchCoveragePercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of branches that are covered by your tests.

nested_items.name: branchesCovered
nested_items.description: The number of conditional branches that are covered by your tests.

nested_items.name: branchesMissed
nested_items.description: The number of conditional branches that are not covered by your tests.

nested_items.name: reportsNotFound
nested_items.description: An array of ARNs passed to BatchGetReportGroups that are not associated with a Report.
(string) ---
